{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a7d7faa-58fc-476f-9402-1afcd7bd37b4","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Target Framework Problems:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Dropped in MSTest v3. End-of-life; you need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Dropped in MSTest v3. End-of-life; you need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net462`** — ✅ Still supported.\n\n**Package Changes:**\nMSTest v3 ships as a single **`MSTest`** meta-package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to:\n1. Update your `TargetFrameworks` — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported TFMs (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. Replace both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` package references with a single `MSTest` package (version `3.x`).\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"787afa89-85b3-4a9b-b0a1-1263de9a0319","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has significant changes in supported frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2 (so net462 is at the boundary — it should be supported)\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET Core 3.1 or later... actually, let me think more carefully.\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x) key changes:\n1. \n\nIt's now shipped as a single package `MSTest` instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages. For the target frameworks, MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and later, but it dropped support for netcoreapp3.1 and net5.0 — only .NET 6.0+ is supported for the modern runtimes.\n\nSo users targeting net5.0 or netcoreapp3.1 will hit compatibility issues, while net462 should work fine. The package references will also need updating to use the single `MSTest` meta-package instead of the separate framework and adapter packages.","outputTokens":716,"requestId":"981B:B2C21:132DF0D:180835B:69FFF28D"},"id":"79ca5843-3475-4f6b-9ab6-f59a81fa9afb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:51:06.497Z","parentId":"fbc542b6-e898-4155-8d45-076513f1c5b8"}
